Eight bidders for 370 tonnes of US stockpiled tin . The U . S . Defense National Stockpile Center said it received bids from eight companies for a total of 370 tonnes of Longhorn grade tin . The lowest bid was $ 2 . 593 per pound for 20 tonnes from M C Canfield . The highest bid was $ 2 . 70 per pound for 5 tonnes from Tin International . LME cash tin settled at the equivalent of $ 2 . 62 per pound on Wednesday . LME deliverable tin is of higher grade than Longhorn . ( ( New York Commodities 212 - 859 - 1646 ) ) 
